Srinagar, 25th June, 2020.

A Police-Public meeting was conducted in Police Station M.R.Gunj, in which Intezamia Committee and Senior Citizens of Khankai Mohalla where present.

The meeting was chaired by the SHO M.R.Gunj Shri Inspr. Gurpurab Singh along with incharge Police Post Urdu Bazar.

The main agenda of the meeting was to seek cooperation from the general public how to deal safely and how not to spread the COVID-19 during business and handling customers, was the point of discussion. During this conversation, the police officials advised the shopkeepers and businessman to take necessary precautions and strictly follow the guidelines issued by the authorities.

SHO appreciated traders working body for their great efforts to deal with COVID-19 during lockdown and also wishing the local market peaceful and successful business ahead.

Moreever the participants were also requested to to make use of masks mandatory and practice social distancing as a norm. 
The meeting ended in good atmosphere with note of thanks. *#HelpUsToHelpU*
